target_text: David Weber, an epidemiologist and infectious disease expert at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill who was not involved with the new research, called the study \u201cexcellent\u201d in an interview with Buzzfeed, but notes that it can\u2019t explain how risky contaminated surfaces are. \u201cDoes that account for 0.01% of transmissions or 15% of transmissions?\u201d Weber says. \u201cWe don't know how frequent it is.\u201d He also cautions that the lab conditions might not precisely recapitulate what happens in the real world
